post_text:
We have identified an issue with a few of the Chromebooks not connecting to the hotspots that were issued. The problem comes from the Chromebook not having received an updated policy since last Wednesday. If you are having trouble getting your Chromebook to connect to your hotspot try this:
1. – Turn off the hotspot
2. – Turn on the Chromebook
3. – Connect to another Internet source (school
campus WiFi, McDonalds, personal phone hotspot, etc).
4. – After getting logged in, open a Chrome browser
5. – Type “ chrome://policy “ (no quotes or
spaces)
6. – Take note of the “Last Fetched:” time.
7. – Hit the “Reload polices” button on the top.
8. – Check the “Last Fetched:” time again.
9. - If it has updated in the last few seconds,
shut down the Chromebook
10. – Power ON the hotspot.
11. – Power ON the Chromebook.
Hopefully the connection will be established automatically without having to enter a WiFi password.

post_text: $1500 Grant For Qualified Families!!
shared_text:
Ajay Pittman is with Shelly Cook Deas and 19 others.
August 14 at 3:57 PM ·

My good friend Ryan Walters and his new organization that he is leading, launched Every Kid Counts Oklahoma which is a grant for low income students who fall below federal poverty line. They can help by assisting with technology and supplement materials.

Visit www.everykidcountsok.org to apply today!

Repost from Every Kid Counts Oklahoma
•
Our students are facing an unprecedented school year as many schools turn to distance learning. Every kid, no matter their financial situation, deserves the opportunity to succeed. Bridge the Gap Digital Wallet will give up to 5,000 low-income families a $1,500 grant to purchase curriculum content and technology for the coming school year. Funds will be awarded on a first-come, first-serve basis. If you or a family you know are in need, visit the link in our bio to apply today!

#bridgethegap #digitalwallet #distancelearning #oklaed #ekco #oklahomaeducation #oklahomaschools
•
#pittman4hd99 #community #Education #virtualeducation #HD99 #repajaypittman #oklahoma #okc

VIRTUAL EDUCATION ENROLLMENT JULY 27-30

Many Parents Have Asked How Anadarko Virtual Education Compares To Various Virtual Charter Schools Throughout The State. Anadarko Schools Provides The Same Quality Of Virtual Education As Provided By The Other Virtual Charter Schools.

On The Plus Side, Anadarko Schools Will Provide You With Educators That Will Know Your Children, Provide Meals Each Day, Give you The Opportunity To Participate In Extracurricular Activities, And Will Also Allow You To Walk Across The Stage And Graduate With Your Anadarko Classmates.

At Anadarko Schools, Students Are More Than Just A Number!

post_text:
GRADUATION 2020

Due to the unprecedented ending of this school year, the Anadarko High School Class of 2020 will have definitely left its mark! This class is certainly deserving of a graduation experience like no class before them. Anadarko Public Schools will do everything possible to make graduation an in person ceremony in which each graduate can share with their families. Currently the timeline is unknown but we are prepared to host graduation sometime into the summer if warranted, with the understanding it might possibly extend into the fall of the next school year. We have some great ideas to honor these graduates in the coming weeks and I am certain our seniors and senior parents will be excited. We will continue to keep you posted.

Currently the timeline is unknown but we are prepared to host graduation sometime into the summer if warranted, with the understanding it might possibly extend into the fall of the next school year. We have some great ideas to honor these graduates in the coming weeks and I am certain our seniors and senior parents will be excited. We will continue to keep you posted.

OSSAA UPDATE

MARCH 17, 2020 – 3:12 p.m. – The OSSAA has been carefully monitoring COVID-19 and following all the recommendations put forth from the CDC. We have also been in contact with State Associations at both a national and regional level.

Yesterday, March 16 the State Department of Education announced mandatory closures of all school facilities; no instruction or activities are permitted at any public school, including Charter and Virtual schools until April 6, 2020.

Thank You Rachel Stephens And Travis Villani!!!!
First Physicians Capital Group (FPCG), who manages rural critical access hospitals like The Physicians Hospital in Anadarko presented Anadarko Public Schools Superintendent Jerry McCormick a donation of 30 Chromebooks totaling nearly $10,000 on Monday, March 9th. The donation will go towards supporting Anadarko Public Schools and their initiative for student Chromebooks.

post_text:
Miss Black Oklahoma Ja'Lyn Yarbrough will be cohosting a Community service event along side the City of Anadarko, Chamber of Commerce and Anadarko Public Schools. The Community Give Back Project will consist of multiple service projects throughout the city. This is a day about investing into Anadarko though volunteerism. This event will be January 20th, Martin Luther King Day at noon. Free lunch will be provided for all participants at the Boy Scout Hut in Randlett Park prior to the event, this will also be the meeting area for all volunteers.

Registration for "Community Give Back Project" now open.

Please click on the following web link (or copy it into your web browser if clicking doesn't work) to go to the signup sheet:

volunteersignup.org/EYR7A

Anadarko High School First Year Robotics Team gladly accepts two checks totaling $3,000.00 from Western Farmers Electric Cooperative of Anadarko and their partnering bank CoBank of Greenwood Village, CO.

Pictured L-R Front: Kyle Johnson, Robotics Student; Lillian Vaughn, Robotics Student; Cody Sims, Robotics Instructor; Gary Roulet, CEO WFEC; Scott Williams, Government Relations and Communications Manager WFEC.

L-R Back : Jerry McCormick, Superintendent APS; Danny Pittman Assistant Superintendent APS.
